branchCategory.description:
&lt;p&gt;Series PF3W7-L digital flow sensor constantly monitors water or coolant flow.&amp;nbsp; &quot;L&quot; models are IO-Link compatible.&amp;nbsp; These sensors also have the &quot;Z&quot; designation for redesigned piping adapters, imparting a 13-53% weight reduction depending on flow range.&amp;nbsp; PF3W7-L features an integrated 3-color, 2-screen display.&amp;nbsp; Options include a manual flow adjustment valve and temperature sensor.&amp;nbsp; The main screen displays instantaneous flow value in red or green, while the white subscreen can show temperture, the switch set point, accumulated or peak/bottom value, or a line name.&amp;nbsp; The display rotates in both clockwise and counter-clockwise directions, offering improved readability during operation.&amp;nbsp; When paired with an IO-Link master, values and settings can be accessed from the HMI screen.&amp;nbsp; PF3W7-L incorporates IO-Link version 1.1 and COM2 speed.&amp;nbsp; 48 bits of process data include flow and temperture values, switch outputs, and diagnostics.&amp;nbsp; Both IO-Link data and switch outputs can be read over the M8 or M8-to-M12 cable.&amp;nbsp; PF3W7-L is IP65 rated, and is both RoHS and CE compliant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

